cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper discusses computer vision methods for crowd analysis tasks such as counting, detection, and tracking. It specifically focuses on density map estimation using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses regression-based methods and proposes metrics for measuring the quality of density maps, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence research, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses tracking, which falls under the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of density maps on low-resolution images, which is relevant to multimedia processing and analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
